has to be wet.

00:22:14.543 --> 00:22:15.418
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:22:18.955 --> 00:22:20.330
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: Masa.

00:22:20.330 --> 00:22:25.930
It has to be corn, but not from
Colombia or-- because that's

00:22:25.930 --> 00:22:28.620
not made from nixtamal.

00:22:28.620 --> 00:22:33.150
It has to be masa harina
from Mexico, Maseca

00:22:33.150 --> 00:22:35.670
or-- what's the other name?

00:22:35.670 --> 00:22:47.720
Maseca or-- I don't remember
the name of the other.

00:22:47.720 --> 00:22:55.200
But it has to be corn,
nixtamalized flour, corn flour.

00:22:55.200 --> 00:22:56.740
That's the secret.

00:22:56.740 --> 00:23:00.670
If it's too white, then
it's not the good one.

00:23:00.670 --> 00:23:03.210
It's light sand color.

00:23:03.210 --> 00:23:05.210
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:23:05.210 --> 00:23:07.270
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: Buy a Mexican one.

00:23:07.270 --> 00:23:12.350
And don't hesitate
to add enough water.

00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:14.990
And if it's too wet,
add a little bit more,

00:23:14.990 --> 00:23:16.660
and no problem.

00:23:16.660 --> 00:23:21.500
It's not like flour
harina that you

00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:23.670
will develop the
gluten, and all this.

00:23:23.670 --> 00:23:26.380
No, this hasn't
got that problem.

00:23:26.380 --> 00:23:29.160
And it's very, very delicious.

00:23:29.160 --> 00:23:33.210
Don't add any salt to it.

00:23:33.210 --> 00:23:34.800
OK?

00:23:34.800 --> 00:23:36.770
Well, something else.

00:23:36.770 --> 00:23:38.270
It's important.

00:23:38.270 --> 00:23:42.580
Here-- I didn't make
enough marinade,

00:23:42.580 --> 00:23:46.540
but normally you have a
lot of marinade left over.

00:23:46.540 --> 00:23:51.360
What you do is you boil it,
reduce it, and then add it

00:23:51.360 --> 00:23:54.890
to the fish, or to the
chicken, or whatever.

00:23:54.890 --> 00:24:03.590
And what you have to do is serve
with-- where's the escabeche?

00:24:03.590 --> 00:24:06.930
You put it on top,
OK, on top, on top.

00:24:06.930 --> 00:24:12.280
And a little bit more
olive oil, and you serve it

00:24:12.280 --> 00:24:14.630
with fried plantain.

00:24:14.630 --> 00:24:18.945
And the plantain,
where are they?

00:24:18.945 --> 00:24:20.430
MALE SPEAKER: [INAUDIBLE]

00:24:20.430 --> 00:24:22.263
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: Yes, over there.

00:24:22.263 --> 00:24:24.410
The blackened, the better.

00:24:24.410 --> 00:24:31.020
You will never eat a--
this plantain is not ready.

00:24:31.020 --> 00:24:31.821
Touch it.

00:24:35.430 --> 00:24:37.110
It's very hard.

00:24:37.110 --> 00:24:42.880
It has to be black, more black,
much more black than that.

00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:46.920
OK, if you-- beans.

00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:47.490
Beans.

00:24:47.490 --> 00:24:50.850
In the southeast of Mexico,
and the south in general,

00:24:50.850 --> 00:24:54.230
we always eat black beans.

00:24:54.230 --> 00:24:58.830
In the north, we
always eat brown beans.

00:24:58.830 --> 00:25:00.380
Yes, yes.

00:25:00.380 --> 00:25:01.900
A little bit of olive oil.

00:25:11.240 --> 00:25:13.315
You have to help
yourselves from here.

00:25:18.430 --> 00:25:24.730
And you can have
your achiote ready.

00:25:24.730 --> 00:25:30.140
Once you dirty your
blender, you buy

00:25:30.140 --> 00:25:33.940
a big piece of achiote
paste, and roast garlic,

00:25:33.940 --> 00:25:37.680
and fresh garlic, and
dry roasted cinnamon,

00:25:37.680 --> 00:25:40.730
and pepper, and oregano--
everything blended

00:25:40.730 --> 00:25:42.520
with vinegar.

00:25:42.520 --> 00:25:45.895
And you make a paste,
like a lighter paste.

00:25:45.895 --> 00:25:51.865
Put it in your fridge, and
you keep it there for months.

00:25:51.865 --> 00:25:54.350
That's it.

00:25:54.350 --> 00:25:54.966
Yes.

00:25:54.966 --> 00:25:55.841
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:02.248 --> 00:26:03.706
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: Mainly.

00:26:03.706 --> 00:26:04.581
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:05.700 --> 00:26:07.200
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: Oh, yes.

00:26:07.200 --> 00:26:08.480
We ate a lot of fish.

00:26:08.480 --> 00:26:09.339
Yes.

00:26:09.339 --> 00:26:10.214
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:16.151 --> 00:26:17.650
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: Well, it

00:26:17.650 --> 00:26:19.490
was before the Spaniards came.

00:26:19.490 --> 00:26:28.190
It was in the 1900s--
no, the 1500s.

00:26:28.190 --> 00:26:32.880
But then they came, and they
brought all the animals.

00:26:32.880 --> 00:26:35.695
So they mixed.

00:26:35.695 --> 00:26:36.570
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:43.859 --> 00:26:45.650
MARGARITA CARRILLO
ARRONTE: I'm not-- well,

00:26:45.650 --> 00:26:48.360
we have a different
system of eating.

00:26:48.360 --> 00:26:51.619
What we do, we have a
very good breakfast--

00:26:51.619 --> 00:26:52.660
not coffee and doughnuts.

00:26:52.660 --> 00:26:58.130
We have eggs, beans,
a heavy breakfast.

00:26:58.130 --> 00:27:03.000
And then just a lunch--
you know, chicken.

00:27:03.000 --> 00:27:07.200
Kids take to school a
sandwich, or something.

00:27:07.200 --> 00:27:12.770
Then we have a very heavy meal
at lunch time, 3:00-- 2:00

00:27:12.770 --> 00:27:17.500
or 3:00 in the afternoon-- but
heavy soup, vegetables, fish,

00:27:17.500 --> 00:27:20.570
whatever, dessert,
and everything.

00:27:20.570 --> 00:27:23.870
And then in the
evening, a light dinner.

00:27:23.870 --> 00:27:29.640
We have like a quesadilla, or
a bowl of cereal, or a yogurt,

00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:31.760
or something light
in the evening.

00:27:31.760 --> 00:27:32.970
It's a different system.

00:27:35.500 --> 00:27:37.650
But the most important
meal is-- yes,

00:27:37.650 --> 00:27:43.030
and we have fish, and a
lot of vegetables, yes.

00:27:43.030 --> 00:27:44.710
But please, it's getting cold.

00:27:44.710 --> 00:27:47.980
So I don't know, what's
the mechanic here?

00:27:47.980 --> 00:27:50.109
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:27:50.109 --> 00:27:52.150
MARGARITA CARRILLO ARRONTE:
OK, there are plates.

00:27:52.150 --> 00:27:53.610
